---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ScrollIndicator from '../../components/ScrollIndicator.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research Team | EES Laboratory & Testing Facility"
  description="Meet the EES research team — the engineers and technicians behind our thermal comfort testing, hydronic ceiling panel development, and energy system innovation."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Research Team</h1>
      <p>The people behind the testing, development, and innovation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Our research team designs, builds, and tests the products and systems that go into every EES installation. Based at our purpose-built <a href="/laboratory/facility">research facility</a> in Moolap, Geelong, the team works across thermal comfort testing, product development, energy system integration, and field performance validation.
      </p>
      <p>
        This isn't theoretical research. Everything we develop gets tested in our full-scale TestCell under controlled, measurable conditions — then installed in real homes and buildings. The research team bridges the gap between lab testing and field performance.
      </p>

      <h2>What the Team Works On</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Thermal comfort testing</strong> — ASHRAE-55 and ISO 7730 compliant testing using calibrated comfort carts, heat flux meters, thermal imaging, and air velocity sensors</li>
        <li><strong>Hydronic ceiling panel development</strong> — designing, manufacturing, and testing our <a href="/laboratory/hydronic-ceiling-panels">radiant ceiling panels</a> for heating and cooling performance</li>
        <li><strong>Heat pump system optimisation</strong> — testing polyvalent heat pump configurations for maximum COP and simultaneous heating/cooling output</li>
        <li><strong>Environmental Service Pod (ESP)</strong> — developing and refining our <a href="/laboratory/environmental-service-pod">integrated modular energy system</a></li>
        <li><strong>Field performance monitoring</strong> — collecting and analysing long-term data from installed systems to validate lab results against real-world conditions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Research-Led Installation</h2>
      <p>
        What makes EES different from other installers is that our installation team and research team are the same company. The insights from testing directly inform how we design and install systems in homes and commercial buildings. When we say a system will perform a certain way, we have the test data to back it up.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our research has been documented in <a href="/laboratory/written-papers">published papers</a> and is available for review.
      </p>

      <h3>Related</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/laboratory/facility">Research facility &rarr;</a></li>
        <li><a href="/laboratory/test-room">Simulation test room &rarr;</a></li>
        <li><a href="/laboratory/written-papers">Research papers &rarr;</a></li>
        <li><a href="/about">About EES &rarr;</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="team-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="team-heading">The Research Team</h2>

      <div class="team-grid">
        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/DrMarkLuther_clean_transparent.png" alt="Mark B. Luther" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Mark B. Luther</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Director (Arch.D. - Architect)</p>
          <p>Honorary Professor of Deakin University after 27 years of service. He specialises in Architecture Science and Environmental Technology. Inventor of the Environmental Service Pod and the Autonomatic Hydronic Ceiling Panel.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/HungQDo_clean_transparent.png" alt="Hung Q. Do" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Hung Q. Do</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Research Development</p>
          <p>PhD candidate specialising in hydronic ceiling innovative systems. His research focuses on effective conditioning through hydronic control in commercial buildings.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/ZhengWang_clean_transparent.png" alt="Dr. Zheng Wang" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Dr. Zheng Wang</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Product Development</p>
          <p>PhD in electrification and decarbonisation of residential buildings. Involved in sizing of off-grid systems for residential projects and product development.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/placeholder.svg" alt="Dr. Murray Herron" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Dr. Murray Herron</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Director</p>
          <p>PhD(2), MUD, MUP, M.Com, GDip GIS, GDip Policy, DE. Brings extensive academic and policy expertise to the research team's strategic direction.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/placeholder.svg" alt="Dr. Jeffrey Godfredson AFSA" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Dr. Jeffrey Godfredson AFSA</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Director</p>
          <p>DBA, MPPM. Contributes leadership and business management expertise to research operations and commercial development.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/LincolnLuther_clean_transparent.png" alt="Lincoln B. Luther" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Lincoln B. Luther</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Manager of Sales</p>
          <p>Over 4 years industry experience in the renewables energy sector with a background in Economics, Banking and Finance. He specialises in solar, battery and renewable building services.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/Matthew Ellison_02_clean_transparent.png" alt="Matthew Ellison" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Matthew Ellison</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Manager of Installations</p>
          <p>Senior electrician experienced in Solar PV and Battery installations in commercial and residential projects. Also involved with electrical research and design on the Environmental Service Pod and Hydronic Control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <ScrollIndicator />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .team-section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .team-heading {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0E2B47;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .team-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .team-member {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .team-member img {
    width: 160px;
    height: 160px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top center;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #fff;
    border: 3px solid #e5e7eb;
    margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    display: block;
  }

  .team-member h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0E2B47;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .team-role {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #2061B7;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .team-member > p:last-child {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .team-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .team-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
